getListItemChangesSinceToken

public java.util.List<SPDocument> getListItemChangesSinceToken(ListState list,
                                                               java.lang.String lastItemID,
                                                               java.util.Set<java.lang.String> allWebs,
                                                               java.lang.String folderLevel)
Used to get list items under a list. If a change token is specified, we only get the changed items. If no change token is specified we get all the items along with the list schema CAML query that is used while calling getListItemChangesSinceToken should only be used for items that are returned and not for the changes. Because if the query stops any itemID to be shown under the changes, web service return the wrong information about the changes on that item. For example, a rename of ID 1 may be shown as deleted or so. Take care of this while making the first call. If you are using a token to get the changes and the CAML query specified may stop some elemnt from getting shown. Do not trust on the change info.

Parameters:
list - : List whose items is to be retrieved
lastItemID - : serves as a base for incremental crawl
allWebs - : A collection to store any webs, discovered as part of discovering list items. Foe example link sites are stored as list items.
folderLevel - : indicates a folder level if we have to start from that folder level. This is possible when some folder has been restored.
Returns:
the list of documents as SPDocument
